      "content": "The argument that nations should ignore the UN when it conflicts with national interest is a pragmatic, yet ultimately self-serving, strategic stance. While some realists might frame it as a legitimate exercise of sovereignty, the broader historical consensus views this unilateral disregard as a direct threat to the international order. Such actions inevitably erode the collective security framework, leading to greater instability and undermining the very rules-based system that benefits powerful states in the long run.",
      "source": "target",
